main event: Mrs. [redacted], a 46-year-old housewife, reported observing 6 unidentified flying objects over Youngstown, Ohio on March 11, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as appearing star-shaped until glasses were worn, then appearing round,The size of the objects was approximated to that of a grapefruit,The sighting lasted for approximately 20 minutes,The objects demonstrated intermittent movement and would generally disappear into the clouds,The investigator concluded the witness was under emotional strain and categorized the case as psychological.
witness description: Mrs. [redacted], a 46-year-old housewife, characterized as psychologically mature but under emotional strain.
